272
00:28:42,800 --> 00:28:45,700
You know those Directors are scary as hell.

273
00:28:46,670 --> 00:28:49,530
If you're thinking of approaching
him, you'd better be careful.

274
00:28:52,870 --> 00:28:54,330
I'm not afraid of anything anymore.

275
00:28:55,370 --> 00:28:59,370
Do you know I almost
got stabbed to death once?

276
00:29:01,100 --> 00:29:03,060
Because back then, I
was dating a complete idiot.

277
00:29:05,430 --> 00:29:06,430
How so?

278
00:29:07,900 --> 00:29:09,500
I don't know why the hell I chose him.

279
00:29:10,300 --> 00:29:11,330
He was so damn stupid.

280
00:29:12,070 --> 00:29:13,430
So stupid he didn't even graduate.

281
00:29:13,730 --> 00:29:15,370
And he acted like some low-life thug.

282
00:29:16,530 --> 00:29:17,600
One day out of the blue

283
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:19,930
someone came looking for him.

284
00:29:20,970 --> 00:29:22,706
And I was also the one in
trouble because of him, dammit!

285
00:29:22,730 --> 00:29:24,200
He came with a knife.

286
00:29:24,570 --> 00:29:25,600
Bursting into his room.

287
00:29:26,170 --> 00:29:26,970
But he found me when he opened the door.

288
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:28,570
You're important to him, aren't you?

289
00:29:28,670 --> 00:29:28,970
No, I'm not.

290
00:29:29,030 --> 00:29:29,600
Tell me!

291
00:29:29,630 --> 00:29:31,130
His brother just walked away.

292
00:29:31,300 --> 00:29:32,300
But I was smart enough.

293
00:29:33,400 --> 00:29:34,470
So I survived.

294
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:35,870
Wanna know what I did?

295
00:29:37,630 --> 00:29:39,070
I egged that guy on

296
00:29:39,500 --> 00:29:41,100
to go down and stab his brother instead.

297
00:29:46,670 --> 00:29:48,430
So what happened to his brother?

298
00:29:50,330 --> 00:29:51,330
I don't know.

299
00:29:51,430 --> 00:29:52,730
Probably dead by now.

300
00:29:56,730 --> 00:29:58,470
Some people are just so damn stupid.

301
00:29:58,800 --> 00:30:00,930
Fucking stupid. Fucking
stupid. Fucking stupid.

302
00:30:29,100 --> 00:30:31,430
You can take the deceased's
belongings back now.

303
00:32:42,400 --> 00:32:44,000
Sky isn't coming today?

304
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:46,600
Doctor, you can talk to me.

305
00:32:52,130 --> 00:32:56,100
From the latest MRI scans, I
still see that the cancer cells

306
00:32:57,000 --> 00:32:59,400
is still spreading throughout
the patient's organs.

307
00:33:00,100 --> 00:33:05,200
That means Ms. Wandee isn't responding to
the targeted therapy we're giving her now.

308
00:33:06,630 --> 00:33:08,100
But if she isn't responding still

309
00:33:09,100 --> 00:33:12,030
we will provide palliative
care from now on.

310
00:33:16,600 --> 00:33:19,700
If I want the new medicine,
how much do I have to pay?

311
00:33:32,830 --> 00:33:34,530
Doctor, get the medicine for my mom now.

312
00:33:34,630 --> 00:33:35,670
I'll bring the money.

313
00:33:36,970 --> 00:33:37,970
Understood.

314
00:33:39,500 --> 00:33:40,530
I'll take my leave now.

315
00:33:48,030 --> 00:33:50,070
What did you say? Someone else?

316
00:33:51,330 --> 00:33:54,870
Yes, is there anyone else who
can access the customer's account?

317
00:33:59,370 --> 00:34:00,630
I'll call you back.

318
00:34:07,870 --> 00:34:08,870
Bank.

319
00:34:15,929 --> 00:34:16,929
Bank!

320
00:34:22,770 --> 00:34:23,830
Shit.

321
00:34:25,900 --> 00:34:26,900
Dammit!

322
00:34:37,130 --> 00:34:38,130
Asshole!

323
00:34:56,630 --> 00:34:57,370
Hello.

324
00:34:57,470 --> 00:34:59,930
I'm calling from the
hospital's finance department.

325
00:35:00,100 --> 00:35:04,000
When can the patient's family come
in to settle the hospital expenses?

326
00:35:06,330 --> 00:35:07,930
And how are you going to pay me back?

327
00:35:10,800 --> 00:35:12,770
I'll do anything you want, Sir.

328
00:35:15,030 --> 00:35:16,030
♪ Sigh ♪

329
00:35:16,830 --> 00:35:19,670
Everybody says this when they come to me.

330
00:35:20,700 --> 00:35:22,140
In the end, can anyone really do it?

331
00:35:22,900 --> 00:35:24,460
That's why I need people like you guys.

332
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:25,960
To keep collecting the debts.

333
00:35:27,500 --> 00:35:29,020
I'll get you the money I promise, Sir.

334
00:35:39,570 --> 00:35:40,570
You know, right?

335
00:35:42,330 --> 00:35:43,870
If you can't pay me back

336
00:35:45,370 --> 00:35:46,570
what will happen to your life?

337
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:20,176
From my perspective, everything that's
ever happened to me has been karma.

338
00:36:20,200 --> 00:36:21,700
Karma from what I did in the past.

339
00:36:22,730 --> 00:36:28,270
Even when Bank ran away with my money,
all I did was work to pay off my debt.

340
00:36:29,070 --> 00:36:30,430
And I keep living my life.

341
00:36:31,670 --> 00:36:33,030
Though I was dead inside.

342
00:36:39,830 --> 00:36:42,400
The cancer is no longer
responding to the medicine.

343
00:36:43,200 --> 00:36:45,330
And multiple organs are failing.

344
00:36:46,530 --> 00:36:54,530
The patient probably
doesn't have much time left.

345
00:37:30,970 --> 00:37:32,500
Some people are just so damn stupid.

346
00:37:32,700 --> 00:37:33,700
Pathetic.

347
00:37:33,900 --> 00:37:35,130
Let's go inside.

348
00:37:35,500 --> 00:37:36,500
I'm starting to get hot.

349
00:37:36,600 --> 00:37:37,600
Me too.

350
00:37:37,700 --> 00:37:38,700
Let's go.

351
00:37:41,500 --> 00:37:45,270
I've felt guilty all along. Thinking I was
the cause of my brother's and mother's deaths.

352
00:37:45,630 --> 00:37:48,100
But it seems the truth isn't like that.

353
00:38:25,330 --> 00:38:26,700
Can I have a cigarette?

354
00:38:34,070 --> 00:38:35,570
I'll just buy one.

355
00:39:07,970 --> 00:39:08,970
Keep the change.

356
00:39:32,300 --> 00:39:33,300
You miscalculated.

357
00:39:34,730 --> 00:39:36,700
Yes, I did.

358
00:39:39,300 --> 00:39:41,270
So that's why I let you keep the change.

359
00:39:43,930 --> 00:39:46,370
I'm charging you two hundred
thousand for that one cigarette.

360
00:39:50,630 --> 00:39:52,470
Are you trying to get
rich from one cigarette?

361
00:39:53,800 --> 00:39:55,320
If you have the guts to buy it from me

362
00:39:56,100 --> 00:39:57,220
then you better be prepared.

363
00:39:58,070 --> 00:40:00,030
The seller can set any price they want.

364
00:40:03,130 --> 00:40:04,930
Better find the money to pay for it.

365
00:40:06,730 --> 00:40:07,730
Mr. 2 Baht.

366
00:40:19,930 --> 00:40:20,930
Is he insane?

367
00:40:24,170 --> 00:40:26,830
So you suddenly became
a saint or something?

368
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:30,070
Maybe I'm doing just that.

369
00:40:30,970 --> 00:40:32,410
Because at the very least, right now

370
00:40:33,400 --> 00:40:35,530
I've completely left that thug life behind.

371
00:40:39,100 --> 00:40:40,970
I try to live my life like everyone else.

372
00:40:41,500 --> 00:40:46,130
Until I heard someone's laughter today.

373
00:40:46,800 --> 00:40:47,970
I egged that guy on

374
00:40:48,030 --> 00:40:49,630
to go down and stab his brother instead.

375
00:40:49,800 --> 00:40:51,500
So what happened to that guy's brother?

376
00:40:52,030 --> 00:40:53,230
Probably dead by now.

377
00:40:56,830 --> 00:40:58,170
Since my brother and mother died.

378
00:40:58,770 --> 00:41:00,410
I never thought about getting my revenge.

379
00:41:01,430 --> 00:41:05,570
But now, everything has changed.

380
00:41:10,500 --> 00:41:11,500
Hello.

381
00:41:13,800 --> 00:41:15,400
You gave me your business card.

382
00:41:18,100 --> 00:41:19,570
I want to be an actor.

383
00:41:38,430 --> 00:41:39,900
I want to be an actor.

384
00:41:41,430 --> 00:41:42,876
P'Sun, would you like try this?

385
00:41:42,900 --> 00:41:44,140
You don't have to call me that.

386
00:41:44,430 --> 00:41:45,606
Just call me Sun is enough.

387
00:41:45,630 --> 00:41:49,630
The only way for you to go through with the
audition is to suck up to the higher ups.

388
00:41:49,830 --> 00:41:54,970
If Kajorn didn't have such a good kid
like you, he wouldn't last this long here.

389
00:41:55,130 --> 00:41:58,100
OMG!

390
00:41:58,970 --> 00:42:00,870
If you are not ready to commit as an actor,

391
00:42:01,030 --> 00:42:03,670
I think you better leave because
it's wasting everyone's time here.

392
00:42:04,070 --> 00:42:05,370
I'm asking you who is it?
